kLinks font-default" id="quickLinks"><div id="tab-navigation" class="sc-d2ee44cb-1 cCgtQI"><ul><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#productdescription" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bRuKDX">Product Description</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#ingredients" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">Ingredients</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#keyuses" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">Key Uses</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#howtouse" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">How To Use</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#safetyinformation" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">Safety Information</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#additionalinformation" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">Additional Information</a><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/medicine/nurokind-od-1500-mcg-tablet-20-TM-TACR1-027793#medfaqsarray" class="sc-d2ee44cb-2 bUlozj">Frequently asked questions</a></ul></div><div id="content-wrapper" class="sc-d2ee44cb-3 dfqbSW"><div id="productdescription"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="Product Description of Nurokind Od Tablet 20" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/productDescriptionIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">Product Description of Nurokind Od Tablet 20</h2></div><div class="content-side-effects"><p style="margin-left:-5px;"><strong>Nurokind-OD Tablet</strong> is used to manage Vitamin B12 deficiency and support healthy nerve function. It helps reduce symptoms such as numbness, tingling sensations, nerve pain, weakness, fatigue, and burning sensations caused by nerve damage or low Vitamin B12 levels. The tablet supports nerve repair, improves red blood cell production, and helps maintain healthy brain and nervous system function.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div><div id="ingredients"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="Ingredients of Nurokind Od Tablet 20" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/ingredientsIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">Ingredients of Nurokind Od Tablet 20</h2></div><div class="content-side-effects"><ul><li><span><strong>Mecobalamin:&nbsp;</strong>Mecobalamin is a biologically active form of vitamin B12 that plays a role in various physiological functions. It contributes to the production of healthy red blood cells, supporting normal oxygen transport in the body. This vitamin is involved in maintaining nerve function by participating in the synthesis of myelin, which forms a protective layer around nerves. Mecobalamin also supports enzymatic processes that help in converting homocysteine into methionine, an amino acid necessary for protein synthesis. Additionally, it plays a role in energy metabolism by assisting in the breakdown of fats and proteins for cellular energy production.&nbsp;</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Other Ingredients:&nbsp;</strong>Excipients q.s.</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id="keyuses"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="Key Uses of Nurokind Od Tablet 20" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/keyUsesIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">Key Uses of Nurokind Od Tablet 20</h2></div><div class="content-side-effects"><ul><li><span><strong>Supports Red Blood Cell Formation:</strong> Mecobalamin contributes to the production of healthy red blood cells, which play a role in maintaining normal oxygen transport throughout the body. This helps sustain overall vitality and well-being.</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Manages Nerve Health:</strong> By participating in the synthesis of myelin, Mecobalamin plays a role in maintaining the structure and function of nerve cells, assisting in the transmission of nerve signals.</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Assists in Managing Neuropathic Pain:</strong> Mecobalamin supports nerve function by managing nerve-related discomfort.</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Maintains Metabolic Processes:</strong> This active form of vitamin B12 is involved in enzymatic reactions that help in breaking down fats and proteins, supporting energy metabolism and overall cellular function.</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Supports Homocysteine Conversion:</strong> Mecobalamin plays a role in converting homocysteine into methionine, which is necessary for protein synthesis and helps maintain normal blood health.</span><br>&nbsp;</li><li><span><strong>Contributes to Overall Well-Being:</strong> By supporting red blood cell production, nerve function, and energy metabolism, Mecobalamin helps maintain physiological balance, contributing to overall health and daily performance.</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id="howtouse"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="How To Use" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/howToUseIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">How To Use</h2></div><div class="content-side-effects"><ul><li><span>As directed by the healthcare professional.</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id="safetyinformation"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="Safety Information" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/safetyInformationIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">Safety Information</h2></div><div class="content-side-effects"><ul><li><span>Read the label carefully before use.</span></li><li><span>Keep out of the reach of children.</span></li><li><span>Store in a cool, dry and dark place below 30°Celsius.</span></li><li><span>Keep away from direct sunlight, heat and moisture.</span></li><li><span>Do not exceed the recommended dosage.</span></li><li><span>Do not chew or crush the tablet, swallow it as a whole with water.</span></li></ul><p><span><strong>Disclaimer:</strong></span></p><ul><li><span>This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure or prevent any disease.</span></li><li><span>Discontinue use and consult your physician in case of any side effects.</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id="additionalinformation"><div class="sc-f2d8a311-0 dbyeOK"><div class="headerWrapper"><img alt="Additional Information" loading="lazy" width="40" height="40" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/additionalInformationIcon.svg" style="color: transparent; max-width: 100%; height: auto;"><h2 class="header">Additional Information</h2></div><div class="sc-f2d8a311-1 ljcpUW"><h3 class="sc-f2d8a311-2 pFxSx">Good to Know</h3><div class="sc-f2d8a311-3 jbNrqX safety-content"><ul><li><span>Nurokind Od Tablet contains Methylcobalamin, the active and highly absorbable form of Vitamin B12.</span></li><li><span>The sublingual route allows faster and more efficient absorption directly into the bloodstream.</span></li><li><span>It is commonly recommended for managing neuropathy, particularly in people with diabetes or neurological symptoms related to B12 deficiency.</span></li></ul></div></div><div class="sc-f2d8a311-1 ljcpUW"><h3 class="sc-f2d8a311-2 pFxSx">Quick Tips</h3><div class="sc-f2d8a311-3 jbNrqX safety-content"><ul><li><span>Incorporate a balanced diet rich in whole foods, including fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span>Aim for a variety of colours on your plate to ensure you’re getting a broad range of nutrients.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span>Additionally, stay hydrated, get regular exercise, and prioritise sleep to support your physical and mental well-being.</span></li></ul></div></div><div class="sc-f2d8a311-1 ljcpUW"><h3 class="sc-f2d8a311-2 pFxSx">Concerns It Can Help With</h3><div class="sc-f2d8a311-3 jbNrqX safety-content"><ul><li><span>Blood health</span></li><li><span>Nerve health</span></li><li><span>Immunity</span></li><li><span>Neuropathic pain</span></li><li><span>Protein synthesis</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div id="medfaqsarray"><div class="sc-66dc78c6-0 fmoSOl"><h2 class="header">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2><div class="sc-66dc78c6-1 cpdUBo"><div class="sc-66dc78c6-2 kThxIr"><h3>What is Nurokind OD Tablet used for?</h3><div><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="18 15 12 9 6 15"></polyline></svg></div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-3 kkyXWF">Nurokind OD Tablet is used to manage vitamin B12 deficiency and nerve-related problems. It helps manage symptoms such as nerve pain, numbness, tingling, weakness, and fatigue. Doctors often prescribe it for neuropathy and conditions where improving nerve health is required.</div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-1 cpdUBo"><div class="sc-66dc78c6-2 kThxIr"><h3>What are the side effects of Nurokind OD Tablet?</h3><div><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-3 ibmVda">Nurokind OD Tablet may cause mild side effects like nausea, headache, and rash. Seek medical attention if you experience severe dizziness, allergic reactions, or vision problems.</div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-1 cpdUBo"><div class="sc-66dc78c6-2 kThxIr"><h3>Does Nurokind OD Tablet cause drowsiness?</h3><div><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-3 ibmVda">Yes, Nurokind OD Tablet might cause mild and temporary side effects, including drowsiness, dizziness or sleepiness. </div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-1 cpdUBo"><div class="sc-66dc78c6-2 kThxIr"><h3>Is Nurokind OD Tablet used for B12 deficiency?</h3><div><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div></div><div class="sc-66dc78c6-3 ibmVda">Nurokind-OD Tablet contains vitamin B12 and is mainly used to manage vitamin B12 deficiency and related nerve disorders such as peripheral neuropathy.</div></div></div></div></div></div><span class="sc-370dd83-6 cNTRYL">Last Updated On 12 Jun. 2026 | 4:27PM (IST)</span><div class="sc-8a9367cb-0 iZTfej font-default"><button class="sc-8a9367cb-1 dTouKa">Report Error</button></div><div class="sc-c57d0c23-1 jUdTz"><h3 class="sectionTitle">Certified Content</h3><div class="sc-8a59f322-0 iISgfK"><p class="pill">Written by</p><figure><img alt="Dr. Nikhil Sharma" loading="lazy" width="56" height="56" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/Picture_1722938697244_37.png" style="color: transparent;"></figure><div class="info"><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/authors-profile/dr-nikhil-sharma-37" class="title">Dr. Nikhil Sharma</a><div class="description">Medical Content Writer | 6 years <span class="degree"><p>M.S Orthopaedics</p></span></div></div></div><div class="sc-8a59f322-0 qmhhr"><p class="pill">Reviewed by</p><figure><img alt="Dr. Mandeep Chadha" loading="lazy" width="56" height="56" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" src="./B12_files/Picture_1695391863575_3.png" style="color: transparent;"></figure><div class="info"><a href="https://www.truemeds.in/authors-profile/dr-mandeep-chadha-3" class="title">Dr. Mandeep Chadha</a><div class="description">Lead Medical Content Reviewer | 12 years <span class="degree"><p>MBBS,  DNB (OBGY)</p></span></div></div></div><p class="editorialPolicy">Check out&nbsp;<a href="https://www.truemeds.in/editorial-policy">Editorial Policy</a></p></div><div class="sc-ebe9d902-0 pNumB"><h2 class="title">Manufacturer details</h2><div class="content">208, Okhla Industrial Estate, Phase-III, New Delhi South Delhi DL 110020 IN<br><br>Country of origin: INDIA</div></div><div class="sc-7775b3eb-0 UcNjp"><div><span class="title">Expiry on or after: </span><span class="content"> November 2026</span></div></div><div class="sc-1e00e9c-0 hsjUK"><div class="title">In case of any issues, contact us:</div><div class="content"><a href="mailto:support@truemeds.in" class="sc-1e00e9c-1 gBYEHV">support@truemeds.in</a><span class="sc-1e00e9c-2 fSTKKb">|</span><a href="tel:09240250346" class="sc-1e00e9c-1 gBYEHV">09240250346</a><div>Address: 6th floor, Urmi Corporate Park Solaris, Saki Vihar Road, Andheri East, Mumbai 400071</div></div></div><div class="sc-2a2774d6-0 iKGvgC font-default"><div class="sc-2a2774d6-1 cIckjI"><div class="sc-2a2774d6-2 lomohT">Was this product description useful?</div><span class="sc-2a2774d6-3 iFQCde">3 people find this information helpful</span></div><button title="Like" class="sc-2a2774d6-4 gjfjZG"><svg class="MuiSvgIcon-root MuiSvgIcon-fontSizeMedium css-vubbuv" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24" data-testid="ThumbUpIcon"><path d="M1 21h4V9H1zm22-11c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2h-6.31l.95-4.57.03-.32c0-.41-.17-.79-.44-1.06L14.17 1 7.59 7.59C7.22 7.95 7 8.45 7 9v10c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h9c.83 0 1.54-.5 1.84-1.22l3.02-7.05c.09-.23.14-.47.14-.73z"></path></svg></button><button title="Dislike" class="sc-2a2774d6-4 fxoDWZ"><svg class="MuiSvgIcon-root MuiSvgIcon-fontSiz